INSERT INTO `Comment` VALUES (1,1,'Kim Rowan','kim.rowan@cancer.org.uk','http://protalk.me','2012-05-19 09:01:36','Awesome site! Great talk too'),(2,1,'Michelle Sanver','michelle@sanver.com','http://www.jippey.com','2012-06-02 13:25:52','I learned a lot from this amazing talk.  Great topic.'),(3,16,'Lineke','lineke@phpassionate.com','http://www.phpassionate.com','2012-06-07 23:11:21','I have seen this talk and it was a very inspiring keynote. Thanks Ian. I will watch it again.'),(4,8,'Kim','kim.rowan@cancer.org.uk','http://n/a','2012-06-10 19:28:50','Brilliant talk from an excellent speaker.  Very clearly explained and really easy to follow along with the slides.  Definitely worth a listen.'),(5,31,'Kim','kim.rowan@cancer.org.uk','http://n/a','2012-06-10 19:31:48','A quick canter through the basic commands of Git and how they differ from similar SVN ones.  Shame time was so tight as some content was skipped - I would have liked to hear more.  A pity also that the Q&A session wasn\'t included at the end of the video.'),(6,28,'Richard Tuin','richardtuin@gmail.com','http://www.rtuin.nl','2012-06-12 14:49:29','This is one of my all-time favourites!'),(7,25,'Kim','kim.rowan@cancer.org.uk',NULL,'2012-06-14 08:51:51','Great introduction to Symfony2, covering all the major parts you\'d need to know.  Engaging delivery and well paced.  Enjoyed it.'),(8,76,'Kim','kim.rowan@cancer.org.uk',NULL,'2012-11-15 11:51:17','Nice talk, well delivered.  Testing is an area I\'m beginning to focus on and I learned a thing or two from this video.  Well worth watching.'),(9,73,'Jane','jane@sugarcat.co.uk',NULL,'2012-11-30 19:23:28','How, exactly do you use image view modes? Do you download anything? Git is command-line based, so how do you view images?'),(10,28,'Skoop','stefan.koopmanschap@gmail.com','http://leftontheweb.com/','2012-12-04 12:41:35','Excellent talk, enjoyed it and learned a couple of things'),(11,103,'kate','zfortsocial@gmail.com',NULL,'2012-12-06 16:35:24','Thanks for sharing! This info was included into a digest of the best PHP news and releases: http://www.zfort.com/blog/php-digest-december-4-2012/ Check it out, I bet this digest is going to be interesting for you!');
