the Elephpant','http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/VoicesOfTheElephpant/~3/vr8b8HFf5Qo/',NULL,'2013-02-15','pend'),(416,1,'2013-02-16','Following on from Code Evolution: Contact Form (part 1), this talk covers setting up the same sort of contact form using Silex instead of creating our own framework.','01:01:11',0,188,'<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/59846954?portrait=0\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>',NULL,NULL,'en','Code Evolution: Contact Form (part 2) – A2LAMP','code-evolution-contact-form-part-2-a2lamp',0,'Its Majax','http://jmather.com/2013/02/19/code-evolution-contact-form-part-2-a2lamp/','http://b.vimeocdn.com/ts/416/130/416130730_640.jpg','2013-02-21','pub'),(417,1,'2013-03-11','In this short video you\'ll learn everything you need to know to get you up and running, so you can start developing amazing Web-Applications using Symfony2 Framework.\r\n\r\nFirst, we\'ll take a look at Composer - incredibly sophisticated but easy to use dependency manager for your PHP projects. Then, we will use Composer to install the Standard Edition of Symfony2 Framework on our local machine. By that time we will be done with the installation part of the tutorial and we will move on to the configuration.\r\n\r\nI will show you how I usually configure my Apache server in order for it to be as close to the production environment as possible. We\'ll then take a look at the most common issue with the new Symfony2 installation - permission problems. I will teach you how to solve this issue using two different techniques.','10:38',0,194,'<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/61061039\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>',NULL,NULL,'en','Installing and Configuring Symfony2','installing-and-configuring-symfony2',0,'Object Oriented PHP','http://object-oriented-php.com/2013/03/installing-and-configuring-symfony2-screencast/','http://b.vimeocdn.com/ts/424/133/424133098_1280.jpg','2013-03-18','pub'),(418,2,'2013-03-27','Jurriaan is leading the development team at Engagor, a social media monitoring and management application built in Gent, Belgium that has PHP and ElasticSearch at its core. Previously Jurriaan worked as lead developer at Netlog. Having worked with web technologies for over several years for these high volume sites have made him experienced in scalability and performance.','54:53',0,109,'<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"315\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/jk9QFvT1Gok\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',NULL,NULL,'en','Introduction To ElasticSearch','introduction-to-elasticsearch',0,'YouTube','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jk9QFvT1Gok','http://img.youtube.com/vi/jk9QFvT1Gok/default.jpg','2013-04-18','pub'),(419,2,'2013-03-27','An introduction to vagrant at PHP Benelux UG Meeting, Mar 2013','29:59',0,175,'<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"315\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/N9QhdrVACRo\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>',NULL,NULL,'en','Introduction to Vagrant','introduction-to-vagrant',0,'YouTube','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N9QhdrVACRo','http://img.youtube.com/vi/N9QhdrVACRo/default.jpg','2013-04-18','pub');
